					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13145200#post-4567963</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13145200/scp-5047#post-4567963</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2020 20:12:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>CornPuffBuddha</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6208004</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm really torn. Just at a glance, it's quite the short article, which isn't necessarily a bad thing, but the narrative didn't hook me. It has a levity that doesn't let me take it seriously, but it's not ridiculous enough to be a joke SCP. It wasn't executed badly, and the concept is <em>fine</em>, but I'm not comfortable with it being a mainlist article.</p> <p>I think this is really just a matter of personal preference, and it didn't hit the spot for me. Hesitant -1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
